<div class="alert alert-info mb-4" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading"><span class="bi bi-info-circle"></span> Type-Safe Navigation Sample</h4>
    <p>
        This page demonstrates MVVM navigation using <code>NavigateTo&lt;TViewModel&gt;()</code> with the interface-based approach.
        The ViewModel implements <code>ITestNavigationViewModel</code> and uses <code>IMvvmNavigationManager</code> for type-safe navigation.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-gear"></span> Features Demonstrated</h6>
            <ul class="small">
                <li><strong>Interface-Based Navigation:</strong> Navigate to ViewModels via interface contracts</li>
                <li><strong>Route Parameters:</strong> Pass relative paths and query strings</li>
                <li><strong>Multiple Routes:</strong> Single component handles multiple URL patterns</li>
                <li><strong>ViewParameter Binding:</strong> Automatic parameter binding from URL to ViewModel</li>
                <li><strong>Query String Processing:</strong> Extract and display query string values</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-diagram-3"></span> Navigation Patterns</h6>
            <p class="small mb-2">Try these buttons to see different navigation patterns:</p>
            <ul class="small mb-0">
                <li><strong>Test:</strong> Basic navigation to <code>/test</code></li>
                <li><strong>Relative Path:</strong> Navigate with path segment</li>
                <li><strong>Query String:</strong> Navigate with query parameters</li>
                <li><strong>Combined:</strong> Both relative path and query string</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <p class="mb-0">
        <span class="bi bi-lightbulb"></span> <strong>Navigation Method:</strong>
        <code>MvvmNavigationManager.NavigateTo&lt;ITestNavigationViewModel&gt;(params)</code>
    </p>
</div>